file.content:
# Laravel Backend Architecture - /app Directory

## Overview

The backend implements a sophisticated business process management and assessment system using Laravel 12 with modern PHP 8.2+ features. The architecture follows Domain-Driven Design principles with clear separation of concerns.

## Directory Structure

```
app/
â”œâ”€â”€ Console/Commands/          # Artisan commands
â”œâ”€â”€ Enums/                    # Type-safe enumerations
â”œâ”€â”€ Http/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Controllers/          # HTTP request handlers
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Middleware/           # Request/response middleware
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ Requests/             # Form request validation
â”œâ”€â”€ Models/                   # Eloquent models
â”œâ”€â”€ Policies/                 # Authorization policies
â”œâ”€â”€ Providers/                # Service providers
â”œâ”€â”€ Services/                 # Business logic layer
â””â”€â”€ Traits/                   # Reusable traits
```

## Core Business Domains

### 1. Business Process Framework

#### Models Hierarchy
```php
BusinessProcessCategory (Strategic/Core/Enabling)
    â†“ hasMany
BusinessProcessProcess (Individual processes)  
    â†“ hasMany
BusinessProcessCore (Process instances/diagrams)
    â†“ hasMany
BusinessProcessActivities (Individual activities)
    â†“ hasOne
BusinessProcessBlueprint (Activity details)

BusinessProcessContent (Versioned content)
    â†“ hasMany  
BusinessProcessContentVersion (Content history)
```

#### Key Models

**BusinessProcessCore** (`app/Models/BusinessProcessCore.php`)
- Central model for process instances
- Manages SOP, RACI, Visual, Swimlane content through polymorphic relations
- Handles version control for all content types
- Implements user ownership and access control

**BusinessProcessActivity** (`app/Models/BusinessProcessActivity.php`)
- Individual process activities with RACI assignments
- Drag-and-drop position management
- Relationships to blueprints for detailed instructions
- JSON fields for flexible RACI data storage

### 2. Assessment System

#### Core Assessment Models

**AssessmentTemplate** (`app/Models/AssessmentTemplate.php`)
- Assessment configurations and metadata
- Soft deletes for template management
- Industry-specific configurations (NAICS)
- Admin-only management with feature flags

**UserAssessment** (`app/Models/UserAssessment.php`)
- User's assessment instances
- Progress tracking and completion status
- Data storage in JSON fields for flexibility
- Relationship to assessment progress tracking

**UserAssessmentProgress** (`app/Models/UserAssessmentProgress.php`)
- Granular progress tracking
- Question-level completion status
- Review flagging system
- Performance analytics data

#### Assessment Questions System

**AssessmentQuestion** (`app/Models/AssessmentQuestion.php`)
- Dynamic question definitions
- Multiple question types (MCQ, NUMBER, TEXT, etc.)
- Conditional logic and dependencies
- Validation rules and constraints

## Controllers Architecture

### RESTful Resource Controllers

**BusinessProcessController** (`app/Http/Controllers/BusinessProcessController.php`)
- Main dashboard and process listing
- Statistics and analytics
- User-specific process filtering

**CoreProcessController** (`app/Http/Controllers/CoreProcessController.php`)
- Process core management (CRUD)
- Content versioning for SOP/Visual/Swimlane tabs
- RACI matrix updates
- Activity management

**AssessmentController** (`app/Http/Controllers/AssessmentController.php`)
- Assessment workflow management
- Progress tracking and validation
- Results calculation and display
- Industry-specific scoring

### Specialized Controllers

**AssessmentFormController** (`app/Http/Controllers/AssessmentFormController.php`)
- Form-specific logic for assessment UI
- Auto-save functionality
- Validation and error handling
- Progressive unlocking logic

**ProcessDiagramController** (`app/Http/Controllers/ProcessDiagramController.php`)
- Legacy support for Level 2 navigation
- Maintains backward compatibility
- Activity management within diagrams

### Admin Controllers

**Admin/AssessmentTemplateController** (`app/Http/Controllers/Admin/AssessmentTemplateController.php`)
- Assessment template management
- Bulk operations for questions
- Feature flag integration
- NAICS industry configuration

**Admin/UserController** (`app/Http/Controllers/Admin/UserController.php`)
- User management with role-based access
- Assessment progress override
- Performance analytics
- System administration

## Services Layer

### Core Business Services

**AssessmentService** (`app/Services/AssessmentService.php`)
```php
class AssessmentService
{
    // Core assessment logic
    public function calculateScore(UserAssessment $assessment): array
    public function getProgressSummary(User $user): array
    public function canAccessAssessment(User $user, AssessmentTemplate $template): bool
    public function generateReport(UserAssessment $assessment): array

    // Industry-specific calculations
    public function applyNaicsAdjustments(array $scores, string $naicsCode): array
    public function calculateBusinessValuation(array $scores, array $profile): float
}
```

**ProgressTrackingService** (`app/Services/ProgressTrackingService.php`)
```php
class ProgressTrackingService  
{
    // Progress management
    public function updateProgress(UserAssessment $assessment, array $data): void
    public function getCompletionPercentage(UserAssessment $assessment): float
    public function getNextRequiredAssessment(User $user): ?AssessmentTemplate

    // Analytics and reporting
    public function getProgressAnalytics(User $user): array
    public function generateProgressReport(UserAssessment $assessment): array
}
```

**ScoringService** (`app/Services/ScoringService.php`)
```php
class ScoringService
{
    // Multi-dimensional scoring
    public function calculateAssessmentScores(array $responses): array
    public function applyWeightings(array $scores, AssessmentTemplate $template): array
    public function generateTierRecommendations(array $scores): array

    // Valuation calculations
    public function calculateEbitdaMultiplier(array $scores): float
    public function getBusinessTier(array $scores): string
}
```

**ValuationCalculator** (`app/Services/ValuationCalculator.php`)
```php
class ValuationCalculator
{
    // Business valuation logic
    public function calculateValuation(array $financials, array $qualitative): array
    public function getMultiplierAdjustments(array $scores): float
    public function generateValuationReport(array $data): array
}
```

## Authorization System

### Policy-Based Access Control

**Core Policies Pattern**
```php
// Example: SOPPolicy
class SOPPolicy
{
    public function viewAny(User $user): bool
    public function view(User $user, SOP $sop): bool  
    public function create(User $user): bool
    public function update(User $user, SOP $sop): bool
    public function delete(User $user, SOP $sop): bool
}
```

**Key Policies**
- **AssessmentPolicy** - Assessment access and progression rules
- **AssessmentTemplatePolicy** - Admin-only template management
- **ActivityPolicy** - Activity CRUD with owner validation
- **DiagramPolicy** - Process diagram access control
- **SOPPolicy** - SOP content management permissions

### Role-Based System (Spatie Permission)
```php
// Roles hierarchy
User -> Admin -> Super Admin

// Key permissions
'view-admin-dashboard'
'manage-assessment-templates'  
'override-assessment-progress'
'manage-users'
'view-system-analytics'
```

## Form Request Validation

### Assessment System Requests

**StoreAssessmentRequest** (`app/Http/Requests/StoreAssessmentRequest.php`)
```php
class StoreAssessmentRequest extends FormRequest
{
    public function rules(): array
    {
        return [
            'assessment_template_id' => 'required|exists:assessment_templates,id',
            'business_name' => 'required|string|max:255',
            'naics_subsector_id' => 'required|exists:naics_subsectors,id',
        ];
    }

    public function authorize(): bool
    {
        return $this->user()->can('create-assessment');
    }
}
```

**AssessmentSubmissionRequest** (`app/Http/Requests/AssessmentSubmissionRequest.php`)
- Dynamic validation based on question types
- Conditional validation for dependent questions
- File upload validation for supporting documents
- Cross-field validation for consistency checks

## Enums for Type Safety

**AssessmentStatus** (`app/Enums/AssessmentStatus.php`)
```php
enum AssessmentStatus: string
{
    case DRAFT = 'draft';
    case IN_PROGRESS = 'in_progress';  
    case COMPLETED = 'completed';
    case ARCHIVED = 'archived';
}
```

**QuestionType** (`app/Enums/QuestionType.php`)
```php
enum QuestionType: string
{
    case MULTIPLE_CHOICE = 'multiple_choice';
    case NUMBER = 'number';
    case TEXT = 'text';
    case TEXTAREA = 'textarea';
    case EMAIL = 'email';
    case SELECT = 'select';
    case SELECT_DEPENDENT = 'select_dependent';
}
```

## Middleware

**AdminMiddleware** (`app/Http/Middleware/AdminMiddleware.php`)
- Restricts access to admin routes
- Integrates with Spatie permission system
- Handles unauthorized access gracefully

**FeatureMiddleware** (`app/Http/Middleware/FeatureMiddleware.php`)  
- Feature flag enforcement
- Controlled rollout of new features
- A/B testing support

**HandleInertiaRequests** (`app/Http/Middleware/HandleInertiaRequests.php`)
- Global data sharing with frontend
- User context and permissions
- Flash message handling
- Appearance theme persistence

## Database Relationships

### Complex Relationships

**Polymorphic Content System**
```php
// BusinessProcessCore has polymorphic content
public function contents()
{
    return $this->hasMany(BusinessProcessContent::class, 'core_id');
}

public function sopContent()
{
    return $this->contents()->where('type', 'sop')->latest()->first();
}

public function visualContent()  
{
    return $this->contents()->where('type', 'visual')->latest()->first();
}
```

**Assessment System Relationships**
```php
// User â†’ UserAssessment â†’ AssessmentTemplate â†’ AssessmentQuestion
// User â†’ UserAssessmentProgress â†’ AssessmentQuestion

class User extends Model
{
    public function assessments()
    {
        return $this->hasMany(UserAssessment::class);
    }

    public function assessmentProgress()
    {
        return $this->hasMany(UserAssessmentProgress::class);
    }

    public function completedAssessments()
    {
        return $this->assessments()->where('status', AssessmentStatus::COMPLETED);
    }
}
```

## Business Logic Patterns

### Assessment Progression Logic
```php
// Progressive unlocking in AssessmentService
public function getNextAvailableAssessment(User $user): ?AssessmentTemplate
{
    $completed = $user->completedAssessments()->pluck('assessment_template_id');

    return AssessmentTemplate::active()
        ->whereNotIn('id', $completed)
        ->where('sequence', '>', $completed->count())
        ->orderBy('sequence')
        ->first();
}
```

