**HandleInertiaRequests** (`app/Http/Middleware/HandleInertiaRequests.php`)
- Global data sharing with frontend
- User context and permissions
- Flash message handling
- Appearance theme persistence

## Database Relationships

### Complex Relationships

**Polymorphic Content System**
```php
// BusinessProcessCore has polymorphic content
public function contents()
{
    return $this->hasMany(BusinessProcessContent::class, 'core_id');
}

public function sopContent()
{
    return $this->contents()->where('type', 'sop')->latest()->first();
}

public function visualContent()  
{
    return $this->contents()->where('type', 'visual')->latest()->first();
}
```

**Assessment System Relationships**
```php
// User â†’ UserAssessment â†’ AssessmentTemplate â†’ AssessmentQuestion
// User â†’ UserAssessmentProgress â†’ AssessmentQuestion

class User extends Model
{
    public function assessments()
    {
        return $this->hasMany(UserAssessment::class);
    }

    public function assessmentProgress()
    {
        return $this->hasMany(UserAssessmentProgress::class);
    }

    public function completedAssessments()
    {
        return $this->assessments()->where('status', AssessmentStatus::COMPLETED);
    }
}
```

## Business Logic Patterns

### Assessment Progression Logic
```php
// Progressive unlocking in AssessmentService
public function getNextAvailableAssessment(User $user): ?AssessmentTemplate
{
    $completed = $user->completedAssessments()->pluck('assessment_template_id');

    return AssessmentTemplate::active()
        ->whereNotIn('id', $completed)
        ->where('sequence', '>', $completed->count())
        ->orderBy('sequence')
        ->first();
}
```

### RACI Matrix Management
```php
// Activity position management
public function updateActivityPositions(array $activities): void
{
    foreach ($activities as $index => $activityId) {
        BusinessProcessActivity::where('id', $activityId)
            ->update(['position' => $index + 1]);
    }
}
```

### Content Versioning
```php
// Automatic version creation on content updates
public function updateContent(string $type, string $content, ?string $summary = null): void
{
    $contentRecord = $this->contents()->firstOrCreate(['type' => $type]);

    // Create new version
    $contentRecord->versions()->create([
        'content' => $content,
        'summary' => $summary,
        'version' => $contentRecord->versions()->count() + 1,
        'created_by' => auth()->id(),
    ]);
}
```

## Error Handling

### Custom Exceptions
```php
// Assessment-specific exceptions
class AssessmentNotAccessibleException extends Exception {}
class AssessmentAlreadyCompletedException extends Exception {}
class InvalidAssessmentProgressException extends Exception {}

// Process management exceptions  
